# Vercel Web Analytics Configuration Update

## Summary
Updated the Vercel Web Analytics configuration to follow the latest official documentation and best practices for Next.js App Router.

## Changes Made

### Modified Files:
1. **src/app/layout.js**
   - Updated Analytics import from `@vercel/analytics/react` to `@vercel/analytics/next`
   - This change aligns with the latest Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router applications

2. **package-lock.json**
   - Updated after running `npm install` to ensure dependencies are properly locked

## Implementation Details

### What Was Already in Place:
- The `@vercel/analytics` package (v2.0.1) was already installed in package.json
- The `<Analytics />` component was already correctly placed in the root layout at the end of the `<body>` tag

### What Was Updated:
According to the latest Vercel Web Analytics Quickstart documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), Next.js App Router applications should import Analytics from `@vercel/analytics/next` instead of `@vercel/analytics/react`.

The documentation specifies:
```javascript
import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';
```

This optimized import provides better integration with Next.js App Router's architecture.

## Testing & Verification

✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ Project builds correctly with `npm run build`
✅ All static pages generated successfully (5 routes)
✅ No new linting errors introduced by this change
✅ Analytics component remains properly positioned in the layout

## Next Steps

To complete the Vercel Web Analytics setup:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics → Select Project → Enable)
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. Verify analytics are working by checking the browser's Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/*` paths
4. Monitor the Vercel dashboard for incoming analytics data after users visit the site

## Notes

The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation's recommendations for Next.js App Router applications. The Analytics component is correctly placed at the end of the body tag in the root layout, which is the recommended position for optimal performance.
